<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The memset(&p, 0, sizeof(p)) is redundant: every pollfd element that can be read later is explicitly assigned (fd, events, revents) before use, and only the first poll_count entries are passed to poll(). Removing this memset would not change program behaviour (the function returns early if poll_count==0 and any accessed entries are initialized). Therefore the memset is an executed operation whose removal would not affect program behaviour — it constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>

